MESSAGE user "What is the default name for newly created rooms, and how can it be changed?"
MESSAGE assistant "The default name for newly created rooms is 'Room'. You can change it by selecting the tag and editing the room field to assign a different name."

MESSAGE user "How do I tag elements?"
MESSAGE assistant "There are several options for tagging elements. To begin, go to the Annotate ribbon and, in the Tag panel, click 'Tag by Category'."

MESSAGE user "What options are available when I start the Tag by Category tool?"
MESSAGE assistant "Several options appear on the Options Bar. You can set the orientation to either horizontal or vertical. Additionally, you can open the Loaded Tags and Symbols dialogue to select the default tags you want to use for each category or load additional tag families."

MESSAGE user "Can I add a leader to the tag?"
MESSAGE assistant "Yes, on the Options Bar, you can choose whether or not to add a leader to the tag. If you include a leader, you can select whether it has an Attached End or a free end. If you attach the leader, you have the option to define its initial length."

MESSAGE user "How do I place a tag?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the element you want to attach it to. Remember, once you select the Tag by Category tool, it remains active automatically, allowing you to continue tagging elements until you finish."

MESSAGE user "What happens if the tag has a leader?"
MESSAGE assistant "The leader will be placed along with the tag. If the leader has a free end, you need to click twice—once to place the leader elbow and a second time to place the tag."

MESSAGE user "What if my tag doesn't have a leader?"
MESSAGE assistant "The tag will be placed directly on the element without a leader."

MESSAGE user "How do I set the correct category for the tag?"
MESSAGE assistant "You’ll go to the 'Create' ribbon and click 'Family Category and Parameters'. Change the category from 'Generic Model' to 'Structural Foundation' and click 'OK'. This makes the relevant parameters for structural foundations available in your tag."

MESSAGE user "How do I add parameters to the tag?"
MESSAGE assistant "Create a label by selecting 'Label' from the 'Create' ribbon. In the label editor, you'll add the shared parameters for foundation dimensions—length, width, and thickness. Shared parameters are essential for tagging, so make sure you select 'Add Parameter' and choose the correct shared parameters for the foundation."

MESSAGE user "What should I do after adding the parameters?"
MESSAGE assistant "Once you add those parameters, you’ll need to adjust the label layout. You can arrange them to display length, width, and thickness, and designate an 'X' to separate them on the same line. You can also change the units to 'Fractional Inches' if you prefer."

MESSAGE user "How do I save and load the tag into my project?"
MESSAGE assistant "Once you're pleased with the tag, save the family and load it into your project by clicking 'Load into Project' on the 'Create' ribbon. Now, your new tag is ready for use in the project."

MESSAGE user "How can I use my new tag in the project?"
MESSAGE assistant "Use 'Tag by Category' or 'Tag All' to apply your newly created tag to the structural foundations in the project."



