MESSAGE user "How do I split a schedule across multiple sheets?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the 'Modified Schedules and Quantities' panel, then click 'Split and Place'. Choose the sheets you want the schedule to appear on, and click 'Split in Place'. You can arrange the schedule evenly across the selected sheets."

MESSAGE user "How do I make sure the schedule appears in the same location on each sheet?"
MESSAGE assistant "Once the schedule is split, go to the 'Project Browser', expand the 'Room Schedule' section, and ensure the schedule is placed correctly on each sheet. You can adjust the placement by selecting the schedule and moving it to the desired position, making sure it's centred or aligned as needed."

MESSAGE user "How can I adjust column widths in the schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the schedule, then use the column width controls. You can drag the column header to the desired width or adjust it so the text doesn’t split across lines. This change will apply to all split sheets as well."

MESSAGE user "How do I split a schedule by levels?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the schedule and use the drag control at the bottom of the schedule to adjust the levels visible on the sheet. You can move the schedule up or down to ensure each level appears on the corresponding sheet."

MESSAGE user "How do I freeze the headers in a schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the 'Modify Schedules and Quantities' ribbon, and click 'Freeze Header' in the Titles and Headers panel. This will keep the headers visible as you scroll through the schedule, making it easier to identify which column corresponds to which parameter."

MESSAGE user "How do I change the units in a schedule column?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the column in the schedule, go to the 'Modify Schedules and Quantities' ribbon,and click 'Format Units' in the Parameters panel. Uncheck 'Use Project Settings', then select your desired unit (e.g., inches). This will apply the unit change to all entries in that column."

MESSAGE user "How do I add a calculated parameter to a schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the 'Modify Schedules and Quantities' ribbon, click 'Insert' in the Columns panel, and choose 'Calculated Parameter'. Name it, choose the parameter type (e.g., area), and create a formula by selecting relevant fields. Then, click 'OK' to apply it to the schedule."

MESSAGE user "How can I add a comments field to a schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the 'Modify Schedules and Quantities' ribbon, click 'Insert' in the Columns panel, and select 'Comments' from the available fields. Move it to the desired position in the schedule and click 'OK' to add it."

MESSAGE user "How do I highlight a schedule item in the model?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the row in the schedule, then go to the 'Modify Schedules and Quantities' ribbon and click 'Highlight in Model' in the Element panel. This will take you to the view showing the selected item, helping you locate it in the model."

MESSAGE user "How do I delete a row from a schedule and its associated element?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the row in the schedule, then go to the 'Modify Schedules and Quantities' ribbon and click 'Delete' in the Rows panel. A message will prompt you to confirm the deletion of both the row and the associated element. Click 'OK' to delete it from both the schedule and the model."

MESSAGE user "How do I create a room data schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the View ribbon tab. In the Create panel, click 'Schedules', then select 'Schedules and Quantities'. From there, search for the 'Room' category, select it, and rename the schedule to 'Room Data Schedule'. Next, add fields like 'Number', 'Name', and 'Level'. In the Sorting and Grouping tab, sort by number and name. Enable a header for grouping by room name and add a blank line between groups. To add furniture, enable the embedded schedule, select 'Furniture', and choose fields like 'Count','Family', and 'Type'. Finally, sort by family and type and uncheck 'Itemise every instance' to group by family and type with a count."

MESSAGE user "How do I filter the room data schedule by sheet?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the room data schedule from the Project Browser. Then, in the properties palette, click 'Edit' next to the filter parameter. In the Schedule Properties dialogue, go to the Filter tab and check the 'Filter by Sheet' box. This ensures that only the objects visible on the sheet the schedule is placed on will appear. Click OK to apply the filter."

MESSAGE user "How do I place a room data schedule onto a sheet?"
MESSAGE assistant "Open the Project Browser and expand the 'Schedules and Quantities' group. Select the room data schedule and drag it onto the sheet view. If the schedule appears too large, zoom out and adjust its position on the sheet. The filter by sheet option allows you to display the schedule with only the rooms visible on that sheet."

MESSAGE user "How do I create a panel schedule template?"
MESSAGE assistant "Expand the 'Panel Schedule Templates' drop-down, then click 'Manage Templates.' In the dialogue, select 'Branch Panel' from the Template type drop-down and choose the 'Two Columns, Circuits Across' configuration. Duplicate the 'Branch Panel (Default)' template, rename it, and click OK. Then, select the renamed template and click 'Edit' to modify template options, such as general settings, loads summary, and the circuit table. Customise the template as needed and click OK to save."

MESSAGE user "How do I edit a panel schedule template?"
MESSAGE assistant "Open the Manage Panel Schedule Templates dialogue from the Manage ribbon. Select the template you want to edit and click 'Edit'. In the Modify Panel Schedule Template mode, use the contextual ribbon to make changes. For example, you can click 'Set Template Options' to adjust settings for width, slots, and parts available in the schedule. You can also modify circuit table options, such as displaying loads and the loads summary section. After making the necessary changes, click OK to save your edits."

MESSAGE user "How do I add a column to a panel schedule template?"
MESSAGE assistant "Open the template for editing. In the panel schedule, click in the Poles field and then expand the 'Insert Column' drop-down in the ribbon. Select 'Right of Selected'. In the new column, click a data cell, then choose the 'Electrical Circuits' category from the drop-down. For the parameter, select 'Connection Type'. To add borders, select all the cells in the new column, go to the 'Cells' panel, and click 'Edit Borders'. In the Edit Borders dialogue, choose 'Outside and Inside' and click OK."

MESSAGE user "How do I apply a template to panel schedules?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the Manage ribbon and open the 'Manage Panel Schedule Templates' dialogue. In the Apply Templates tab, select the panel schedules you want to apply the template to. Then, choose the template from the list and click 'Update Schedules'. If necessary, a warning dialogue will appear regarding the schedule data associated with the panels. The selected panel schedules will apply the template once the update is complete."

MESSAGE user "How do I split a door schedule across multiple sheets?" 
MESSAGE assistant "Ensure you have the sheets created for each floor. Then, open the door schedule and use a filter to display only the doors for the relevant level. After that, place the schedule on the right sheet and limit it to that level's doors."


MESSAGE user "How can I highlight doors below a certain width in a schedule?" 
MESSAGE assistant  "You can highlight doors below a certain width by using conditional formatting. Go to the Properties palette, click the edit button next to 'Formatting', select 'Width', and set a condition for 'Less Than' a specific value, such as 30 inches. Then, choose a colour, like red, to highlight those doors."


MESSAGE user "How do I check the model for a door highlighted in a schedule?" 
MESSAGE assistant "Select the door from the schedule, then go to the 'Modify Schedules and Quantities' ribbon. Click 'Highlight in Model', and the view will zoom in on the door in the model. You can then inspect the door in the context of the project."


MESSAGE user "How do I change the door size after highlighting it in a schedule?" 
MESSAGE assistant "Select the door in the model, then choose the appropriate door type from the type selector, such as a 36-inch by 84-inch door. Adjust any temporary dimensions to fit it properly in the model."


MESSAGE user "How do I filter a door schedule to only show doors visible on the sheet?" 
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the Properties palette, click the edit button next to 'Filter', and choose 'Filter by Sheet'. Then, click 'OK' to apply the filter and only display the doors visible in the specific view."


MESSAGE user "How do I format a door schedule on a sheet?" 
MESSAGE assistant "Drag the schedule from the project browser into the view, align it with the top, and zoom in to see only the floor's relevant doors. You can further format the schedule to match your desired appearance."


MESSAGE user "How can I change the number of single-pole breakers in a panel schedule?" 
MESSAGE assistant "Select the panel schedule and edit the property for the 'Maximum Number of Single-Pole Breakers'. Adjust the value, and the panel schedule will update accordingly."


MESSAGE user "How do I add a new column in a panel schedule template?" 
MESSAGE assistant "Select the column heading where you want to add the new column, then go to the ribbon and choose 'Insert Column' to add it to the left or right of the selected column."


MESSAGE user "How do I change the alignment of text in a panel schedule?" 
MESSAGE assistant "Highlight the cells you want to modify, and then in the ribbon, select the 'Text Alignment' options to set horizontal and vertical alignments, such as 'Centre' for horizontal and 'Bottom' for vertical."


MESSAGE user "How do I apply a custom panel schedule template?" 
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the 'Manage' tab of the ribbon, select the 'Panel Schedule Templates' dropdown, and choose 'Change Template.' Select your desired template, such as the 'Commercial Template', and click 'OK' to apply it."

MESSAGE user "How do I create a room schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the View ribbon, and in the Create panel, click on the Schedules drop-down. Select 'Schedules and Quantities', then choose the room category. After that, add the required parameters, like level, name, number, and area, to the scheduled fields and configure the sorting and grouping. You can also add grand totals and adjust the appearance as needed before clicking OK to generate the schedule."


MESSAGE user "How can I hide not-placed rooms from my schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the Modify Schedules and Quantities ribbon tab, and in the Not Placed Unenclosed Rooms panel, click 'Hide'. This will remove any rooms that are not placed in the model from the schedule."


MESSAGE user "How do I filter rooms in my schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the Properties palette and click the 'Edit' button next to the Filter option. Choose the 'Name' parameter and set the filter to 'Does not equal' services or storage, depending on the rooms you want to exclude. After applying the filter, click OK to update the schedule."


MESSAGE user "How can I change the appearance of my room schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the Properties palette and click the 'Edit' button next to 'Appearance'. You can adjust settings like stripe rows, font type, and size. You can also change the title text to a different font or style. Once you're happy with the changes, click OK to apply them."


MESSAGE user "How do I delete unwanted rooms from my schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the first room, then hold down the Shift key to select the last room. With all the unwanted rooms selected, go to the Modify Schedules and Quantities ribbon tab and click the 'Delete' button. Confirm the deletion, and those rooms will be removed from the schedule."


MESSAGE user "How can I change the text size in my schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the column you want to adjust. Then, go to the Appearance panel in the Modify Schedules and Quantities ribbon, click the Font tool, and adjust the size. You can also make the text bold or choose other font options. Click OK to save the changes."


MESSAGE user "How do I group columns in my schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the columns you want to group together by holding the mouse button down and dragging across them. Then, go to the Modify Schedules and Quantities ribbon tab and click 'Group' in the Title and Headers panel. You can then enter a title for the group, such as 'Dimensions'."


MESSAGE user "How do I centre the data in my schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the entire table by clicking and dragging across all the columns. Then, go to the ribbon and set the horizontal alignment to 'Centre' and the vertical alignment to 'Middle'. This will centre all the data in the cells."


MESSAGE user "How do I apply borders to my schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the entire table in your schedule. Then, go to the appearance panel in the Modify Schedules and Quantities ribbon and click the 'Borders' button. Choose your desired line style for the outer border and the internal lines, then click OK to apply the changes."


MESSAGE user "How do I copy a schedule to another sheet?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the schedule on the current sheet. Then, go to the Modify ribbon tab, click 'Copy to Clipboard', and from the Paste drop-down, select 'Align to Selected Views'. Choose the sheets you want to place the schedule on and click OK. The schedule will appear on the selected sheets."

MESSAGE user "What is a key schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "A key schedule allows us to create groups of parameter values and assign them to objects. For example, you can group finishes for rooms like bedrooms or bathrooms under key names such as 'Bedroom Finishes' and 'Bathroom Finishes' and apply them to the relevant rooms."


MESSAGE user "Why would you use a key schedule for doors?"
MESSAGE assistant "A key schedule for doors is useful when you have multiple doors requiring similar hardware, such as handle types, lock types, and the number of hinges. By grouping them under key names like 'Group 1', 'Group 2', etc., you can easily assign hardware values to multiple doors at once, saving time and reducing the risk of errors."


MESSAGE user "How do you create a key schedule for doors?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the View ribbon, click on 'Schedules' > 'Schedules and Quantities'. Select the door category, then choose 'Schedule Keys' and name the schedule, such as 'Door Hardware'. Add fields for parameters like handle type, number of hinges, lock type, and others, and then click OK."


MESSAGE user "How do I add custom parameters to a key schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Click the 'Add Parameter' button in the Schedule Properties dialogue. You can create a new parameter by selecting 'New Parameter', setting the parameter type, and then adding it to the fields. For example, you can add a 'Lock Type' as a text parameter or a 'Requires Closer' as a Yes/No parameter."


MESSAGE user "How do I add data to a key schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the 'Modify Schedule/Quantities' ribbon, click 'Insert Data Row', and start entering the key values for each group, such as handle type, lock type, and the number of hinges. You can add multiple rows for different hardware groups, like Group 1, Group 2, and Group 3."


MESSAGE user "How do you assign a key to a door?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the door in the plan view, and in the Properties palette, find the 'Hardware Group' parameter. Choose the appropriate key group from the list, such as 'Group 1', and the door will automatically inherit the hardware values from that key schedule."


MESSAGE user "How do I update the data for doors in a key schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go back to the key schedule, make changes to the values (for example, changing the number of hinges), and the updates will automatically propagate to the doors that have been assigned to that key group in the model."


MESSAGE user "Can I add the hardware group to a door schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Yes, you can add the hardware group to a door schedule. Go to the 'Modify Schedule/Quantities' ribbon, click the 'Insert' button, and select 'Hardware Group' from the available fields. Once added, the door schedule will display the hardware group for each door in the project."


MESSAGE user "How do I group windows in a schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the Properties palette, click 'Edit' next to the 'Sorting and Grouping' parameter, and choose to sort by 'Level' first and then by 'Mark'. This will organise the windows by the level they are placed on and their mark values."


MESSAGE user "How do I hide a column in a schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the column you want to hide, then go to the 'Modify Schedule/Quantities' ribbon, click on the 'Columns' panel, and select 'Hide Columns.' This will remove the column from the view but still keep it for sorting and grouping purposes."


MESSAGE user "How do I filter the fields for a window schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the Schedule Properties dialogue, open the 'Filter' panel, and select the type of parameters you want to display. For example, you can filter for 'Built-in Parameters' or 'Length Parameters' to narrow down the available fields."


MESSAGE user "What type of parameters should I add to a window schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Typically you would want to add built-in parameters like 'Level', 'Mark', 'Width', 'Height', 'Seal Height', and 'Family and Type'. These fields provide critical information for documenting the windows in the model."


MESSAGE user "How do I add columns to a window schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the 'Modify Schedule/Quantities' ribbon, click on the 'Insert' button in the Columns panel, and select the parameters you want to add, such as 'Handle Type' or 'Lock Type'. After adding them, click OK to update the schedule."


MESSAGE user "How do I update values for the hardware group in the schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Change the hardware group assignment for the doors in the Properties palette. Updates to the hardware group will reflect automatically in the door schedule."


MESSAGE user "What happens if I update a parameter in a key schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "The changes are automatically applied to all assigned to that key group. This helps maintain consistency and reduces the need for manual updates across the entire project."


MESSAGE user "How do I create a rebar bending schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the View tab, and in the Create panel, select 'Schedules' > 'Schedule Quantities'. In the New Schedule dialogue, under Category, select 'Structural Rebar' and then click OK. You can customise the fields and sorting options as needed."


MESSAGE user "How do I add fields to a rebar schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "In the Schedule Properties dialogue, under 'Available fields', select the fields you want to include. Click the 'Add parameter(s)' button to add them. If you want to select multiple fields, hold the CTRL or SHIFT keys while selecting."


MESSAGE user "How do I change the order of fields in my schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "In the Schedule Properties dialogue, you can use the 'Move up' and 'Move down' buttons to reorder the fields in your schedule."


MESSAGE user "How do I sort data in my schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Click on the 'Sorting/Grouping' tab in the Schedule Properties dialogue. From the 'Sort By' drop-down menu, choose the parameter you want to sort by. You can also select whether to display the sorting parameter as a header or footer on your sheet."


MESSAGE user "How do I format fields in my rebar schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Click the 'Formatting' tab in the Schedule Properties dialogue. Select the field you want to format and adjust its settings, such as text alignment or number formatting. Click OK to apply your changes."


MESSAGE user "How do I add a rebar schedule to a sheet?"
MESSAGE assistant "In the Project Browser, right-click 'Sheets (All)' and select 'New Sheet'. Once the new sheet dialogue appears, click OK. Then, drag your new rebar schedule from the Project Browser and drop it onto the sheet."


MESSAGE user "What do I do when my rebar schedule is too long for the sheet?"
MESSAGE assistant "You can click the break symbol on the right edge of the schedule to break it into segments. Additionally, you can widen the columns to make sure the headers fit."


MESSAGE user "How do I create a space schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select 'Schedules' > 'Schedule Quantities' from the View tab. Choose 'Space' as the category and select the fields you want to include, such as space name, number, volume, and air changes per hour. Click OK to generate the schedule."


MESSAGE user "How do I combine parameters in a space schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Click the 'Edit' button in the Fields section of your schedule. Select 'Combined Parameters', give the combined parameter a name, and choose the parameters you want to combine, such as the space name and number. Remove any unwanted separators, and click OK."


MESSAGE user "How do I create a calculated parameter in a schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Click the 'Edit' button in the Fields section of your schedule and select 'Add Calculated Parameter'.  Name the calculated parameter and define the formula you want to use. For example, divide the actual supply airflow by the space volume, then click OK."


MESSAGE user "How do I format the calculated parameter in the schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Click the 'Edit' button under the 'Formatting' tab. Select the field you want to format and adjust the decimal places or other settings. For example, you can set the decimal places to zero for the calculated air changes per hour."


MESSAGE user "What are the areas labelled in the floor four zone of the area plan?"
MESSAGE assistant "The areas in the floor four zone are labelled as office space, circulation, core, another office space in the tower, and an atrium at the end of the building."


MESSAGE user "How do you create an area schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Click the Schedules dropdown, and select 'Schedules and Quantities'. Then, choose 'Areas', add necessary fields like name, level, and area, and sort and group by name and level."


MESSAGE user "What should you do to calculate the total area in a schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the area field and choose 'Calculate Totals' to display the total area in the schedule."


MESSAGE user "How do you round the area field to the nearest square foot in the schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "To round the area field, edit the field format in the Properties palette, uncheck 'Use Project Settings', set the rounding to zero decimal places, and change the unit symbol to 'sf' for square feet."


MESSAGE user "What is the purpose of applying a colour scheme to the area plan?"
MESSAGE assistant "The purpose of applying a colour scheme is to visually distinguish different areas based on their name or function, which helps in understanding the layout and zoning of the building."


MESSAGE user "How do you create a new colour scheme for areas?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the colour fill legend, click 'Edit Scheme', duplicate the scheme, and set it to colour by the area name parameter, adjusting the colours as needed for each zone."


MESSAGE user "How do you apply a colour scheme to multiple views?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the Annotate ribbon, add a colour fill legend, and choose the desired colour scheme (like 'Area Name') to be applied to the areas in that view."


MESSAGE user "What is the benefit of importing schedules from another model?"
MESSAGE assistant "Importing schedules from another model helps save time and ensures consistency between projects, as it allows you to reuse previously created schedules."


MESSAGE user "How do you import schedules from another project?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the Insert ribbon tab and click 'Insert Views from File', browse to the project file with the desired schedules, and select the schedules to import into your current model."


MESSAGE user "When I import schedules from another model, what happens to the data?"
MESSAGE assistant "When schedules are imported, the column headings, formatting, and grouping from the original model are preserved, but the data reflects the current model's information."


MESSAGE user "How can you export a schedule to a spreadsheet?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the schedule view, go to the File menu, choose 'Export', then select 'Schedules'. Save the file as a CSV, and it can be opened in Excel for further manipulation."


MESSAGE user "What options are available for customising the export of a schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "When exporting a schedule, you can choose which title and column headers to include and specify the delimiter for the data (e.g., a comma for CSV files)."


MESSAGE user "How can you manipulate an exported schedule in Excel?"
MESSAGE assistant "Once the schedule is exported to a CSV file, you can open it in Excel and manipulate the data as needed without affecting the original Revit model."


MESSAGE user "What is the advantage of exporting a schedule to a spreadsheet?"
MESSAGE assistant "Exporting a schedule to a spreadsheet allows you to combine, analyse, or manipulate the data outside of Revit, offering flexibility in data handling without altering the model."

MESSAGE user "What is a schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "A schedule is simply another way of displaying a building model. When you make changes to the model that affect items in the schedule, the schedule immediately updates, or vice versa."


MESSAGE user "How do I create a schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Click 'Schedule/Quantities' to open the New Schedule dialogue and select the category of elements that you want to schedule."


MESSAGE user "Can I filter the categories I see in the New Schedule dialogue?"
MESSAGE assistant "Yes, to help reduce the number of categories you see, you can expand the 'Filter' list and select or deselect disciplines to show or hide their categories."


MESSAGE user "What's next after naming the schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Next, choose 'Schedule building components' and leave the phase set to 'New Construction'. Then click OK."


MESSAGE user "How do I add fields to the schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Now, select the available fields you want to include, and then click 'Add parameter(s)' to place them into the 'Scheduled fields (in order)' list."


MESSAGE user "How do I change the order of the fields in the schedule?"
MESSAGE assistant "Once all the fields have been placed into the 'Scheduled fields' list, their column order from left to right in the resulting schedule determines their appearance. To change this order, select the field you want to move, then click 'Move parameter up' or 'Move parameter down'."



