MESSAGE user "What happens if I set calculation types to 'Performance' in duct system properties?"
MESSAGE assistant "Setting the calculation type to 'Performance' improves Revit's handling of large duct networks but disables duct sizing tools for that specific system."


MESSAGE user "How can I change the appearance of duct system types?"
MESSAGE assistant "By accessing 'Type Properties' and editing the 'Graphics Overrides' section, where you can adjust line patterns, colours, and line weights."


MESSAGE user "Can I change the system classification of a duct system?"
MESSAGE assistant "No, the system classification (e.g., exhaust air, supply air, return air) cannot be altered. Each system type is locked to its classification to prevent incorrect assignments."


MESSAGE user "How do you create a new duct type?"
