MESSAGE user "What are routing preferences in duct and pipe types?"
MESSAGE assistant "Routing preferences define the specific fittings used for a duct or pipe type, including elbows, transitions, tees, and other components. You can edit routing preferences in the 'Type Properties' dialogue box."


MESSAGE user "How do I test and compare different duct types?"
MESSAGE assistant "To compare duct types, create duct runs using each type and observe differences in fittings like elbows and transitions. For example, you might compare a duct type with a 90-degree elbow versus one with a radius elbow."


