MESSAGE user "How do I adjust the core boundary of a wall assembly?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the wall's type properties and in the structure tab, you can move the core boundaries to control which layers meet at the junction. For the screen wall, move the core boundary to include only the metal stud, and for the external wall, adjust the core boundary to include the insulation layer."


MESSAGE user "How do I use the railing tool to create a fence?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the Architecture ribbon and click on the Railing tool under the Circulation panel. Then, choose the fence post and board type. Set the base level to the second floor and use the 'Pick Lines' tool to trace the wall path for the railing."


MESSAGE user "How do I change the thickness of a tapered wall?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the wall and open its type properties. Under the Cross Section parameter, change it from vertical to tapered. Adjust the exterior angle to your preferred degree. Then, you can drag the control at the bottom of the wall to modify the angle."


MESSAGE user "How do I modify the slope of a railing to follow a wall?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the railing and go to the Modify tab. From the Tools panel, click 'Pick New Host' and select the wall. The railing will now follow the slope of the wall."


MESSAGE user "How can I add a post at a change in angle in a railing?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the railing and click 'Edit Path' under the Modify Railing tab. Use the 'Split Element' tool to break the railing at the angle change. Once done, click 'Finish Edit Mode' to apply the change, and a post will appear at the angle."


MESSAGE user "How do I apply a variable thickness to a wall layer?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the wall’s type properties and click 'Edit' nextto the Structure parameter. Inthe assembly, select the layer you want to change (like the concrete layer), and check the 'Variable' box. Only one layer can be setas variable, so ensure no other layers are marked as variable."


MESSAGE user "How do I set the exterior angle of a tapered wall?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the type properties of the wall, and in the Cross Section panel, change the cross section definition to 'Tapered'.  Then, set the desired exterior angle. You can further modify the angle interactively by dragging the control at the bottom of the wall."


MESSAGE user "How do I adjust the junction between two walls?"
MESSAGE assistant "To adjust the junction between two walls, ensure their core boundaries are positioned correctly. Adjust the core boundary of each wall to control how the layers meet. You may need to change the priority of layers to achieve the correct junction."


MESSAGE user "How do I distribute windows evenly along a wall?"
MESSAGE assistant "Zoom into the area  and go to the Annotate tab. Select the Aligned Dimension tool from the Dimension panel. In the options bar, choose 'Wall Centerline' and select 'Two Faces'.  Pick the external face of the left-hand wall to start, and then select the centres of the windows. Select the left side of the door opening, and click in an empty space to place the dimension. Click the EQ symbol to enable the EQ constraint, which will evenly distribute the windows along the wall."


MESSAGE user "How do I adjust wall placement after enabling the EQ constraint?"
MESSAGE assistant "Click 'Modify' fromthe ribbon. This allows you to drag the left-hand wall, and the EQ constraint will maintain the even distribution of windows. You can see the effect of moving the wall while the EQ constraint keeps the windows spaced evenly. If you want to undo changes, click 'Undo' on the Quick Access Toolbar."


MESSAGE user "How do I remove the EQ constraint temporarily?"
MESSAGE assistant "Click on the dimension and then click the EQ symbol. This will disable the constraint and allow you to see the actual dimensions. If you move the wall again, the EQ constraint will no longer apply. You can re-enable it by clicking on the EQ symbol again."


MESSAGE user "How do I make the dimensions visible while keeping the EQ constraint active?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the dimension and right-click. From the shortcut menu, choose 'Turn off EQ Display.' This will display the actual dimensions while keeping the EQ constraint in effect, so the windows remain evenly distributed as you adjust the wall."


MESSAGE user "How do I add and centre a door between two walls?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the Architecture tab and select the 'Door' tool from the Build panel. Place the door along the wall. Then, go to the Annotate tab and choose the Aligned Dimension tool. Select the outer faces of both walls and the centre of the door. Move your cursor into an empty space and click. Finally, click the EQ symbol to enable the EQ constraint, ensuring the door is centred between the two walls."


MESSAGE user "How do I create a structural wall?"
MESSAGE assistant "Open a new project using a structural template. On the Structure ribbon, in the Structure panel, click 'Wall: Structural'.  Expand the Type Selector and choose the type of wall, such as the Generic 300mm wall. In the Modify Place Structural Wall contextual ribbon, ensure 'Line' is selected under the Draw panel. In the Options Bar, choose 'Height' and set it to the desired level. Click to place the start point, then move the cursor and click to set the endpoint. Press ESC to complete the wall placement."


MESSAGE user "How do I add doorsand windows to a curtain wall?"
MESSAGE assistant "You need to load curtain wall-specific door and window families first. Go to the Insert ribbon tab, then from the Load from Library panel, select 'Load Family'. Search for the curtain wall doors and windows in the content browser, select the ones you want, and click 'Load'. After that, select a panel on the curtain wall and swap it for the loaded family."


MESSAGE user "How can I change the size of a curtain wall panel for a door?"
MESSAGE assistant "Use the Curtain Grid tool. Select the panel, then divide it horizontally and vertically using temporary dimensions to fit the size of the door. After adjusting the grid to the correct size, place the door into the panel, and it will automatically adjust to fit."


MESSAGE user "How do I modify the mullions in a curtain wall?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the mullion you want to adjust. If needed, unpin it from the type properties, then change its size in the type selector. You can also delete any unnecessary mullions, like the one at the bottom of a door panel, or adjust the size of the vertical mullions to fit the design."


MESSAGE user "What do I do if I don't want the screen wall to join with the existing external wall?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the screen wall, then right-click at the end of the wall and choose 'Disallow Join'. After this, you can trim or extend the screen wall to meet the external wall without creating a joint."


MESSAGE user "How do I unlock and extend finish layers in a wall type?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the wall and go to its Type Properties. Click 'Edit' next to the structure parameter. In the assembly, select the finish layers, then unlock their top edges by clicking the padlock icon. After unlocking, you can extend the finish layers separately from the main structure of the wall."


MESSAGE user "How do I make sure the finish layers extend in front of the roof for a clean junction?"
MESSAGE assistant "Select the walls with the finish layers, then set their top extension distance parameter to the desired value, such as 1 ft. This will align the finished layers to the top of the roof and create a cleaner junction."


MESSAGE user "How do I adjust the junction where two walls meet?"
MESSAGE assistant "Access the wall’s Type Properties and modify the core boundaries or other layers within the structure. You can change the priority and function of layers such as air or metal stud layers to achieve the desired junction."


MESSAGE user "How do I move an air layer outside the core boundary?"
MESSAGE assistant "Go to the wall’s assembly in the Type Properties and select the air layer. Use the 'up' or 'down' button to position the air layer outside the core boundary, which will adjust the core boundaries correctly."


MESSAGE user "How do I create a new wall type?"
